text=(:title PmWiki Installation Notes:)%0a!! Install Notes%0aLooking for a simple, configurable, and cross-platform wiki engine, I found PmWiki. I will configure it to run on http://localhost/wiki with shared filebase under both Ubuntu 16.04 and Windows 10. I'll utilize a shared writable NTFS drive to store the wiki. I want clean urls, userauth, public/private bifurb, reskin, and tarball backups.%0a%0a!!! Windows 10%0a* Unziped to @@E:\pmwiki-2.2.98@@%0a* Installed IIS (Windows components)%0a* Installed PHP Manager for IIS%0a** Installed .NET 2.0%0a** Registry hack, see: [[https://stackoverflow.com/questions/21216228/php-manager-for-iis-fails-to-install]]%0a* Added @@DefaultAppPool@@ with '@@Read@@' on @@E:\pmwiki-2.2.98@@ and '@@Full Control@@' on @@wiki.d@@\ and @@uploads@@\ subdirectories%0a* Added pmwiki.php as defaultDocument, and pmwiki.php rewrite rule to @@Web.config@@%0a%0a!!! Ubuntu 16.04%0a* Installed Apache & PHP%0a** @@apt-get install apache2 php7.0 libapache2-mod-php@@%0a** (optional) @@apt-get install php-pear@@%0a** (optional) replace default index.html with blank page%0a### @@cd /var/www/html/@@%0a### @@sudo mv index.html index.default.html@@%0a### @@sudo cat > index.html@@%0a[@%3c!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd"%0a%3chtml xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">%0a%3chead>%0a%3cmeta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1" />%0a%3ctitle>%3c/title>%0a%3c/head>%0a%3cbody>%0a%3c/body>%0a%3c/html>@]%0a%0a* Updated NTFS filesystem mount permissions%0a## @@sudo vi /etc/fstab@@ update @@/media/Extra@@ to: @@gid=33@@ (www-data)%0a## @@sudo umount /media/Extra; sudo mount /media/Extra@@%0a%0a* Linked PmWiki%0a## @@cd /var/www/html ; sudo ln -s /media/Extra/pmwiki wiki@@%0a%0a* Enabled @@mod_rewrite@@%0a## @@sudo a2enmod rewrite@@%0a## @@cat > /var/www/html/wiki/.htaccess@@%0a[@# Use mod_rewrite to enable "Clean URLs" for a PmWiki installation.%0aRewriteEngine On%0a# Define the rewrite base.%0aRewriteBase /wiki/%0a# Send requests to pmwiki.php, appending the query string part.%0aRewriteRule ^([A-Z0-9\xa0-\xff].*)$ /wiki/pmwiki.php?n=$1  [QSA,L]%0a@]%0a%0a* Enabled @@.htaccess@@%0a## @@sudo vi /etc/apache2/apache2.conf@@ %3c%3c%0a[@%3cDirectory /var/www/html/wiki/>%0a        AllowOverride FileInfo%0a%3c/Directory>@]%0a%0a!!! Tested, working!
